<subSubSection id="4A15020F6785DD00BB34F85C3440E1BA" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="type">
<paragraph id="3EB337D72E416B815C57A4249D73C614" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E49BF82B145B36A33A9D9BF542C941C" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Based on 
<taxonomicName id="74533823F32637AED954047F5BCDD5F2" authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" form="inermis" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hystrix subsp. forma" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="hystrix" subSpecies="forma">Convolvulus hystrix forma inermis</taxonomicName>
Chiov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8A935768ACD124EF090F154EDC3C729" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="1ADBCCEE4D9D92A40DD32D10484602EA" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C98840D555659A2D765EC9CB221F345C" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Plant virtually unarmed, the side branches long, relatively slender, spinescent when old, short lateral branchlets absent or, when present, neither rigid nor spine-like. Indumentum and flower heads similar to 
<taxonomicName id="62ADFECDAC392633A2053207ACF86B5D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="hystrix" subSpecies="hystrix">subsp. hystrix</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6EEE983266DFDF712B8DF34C9BA230E" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="92B2F26F3415D15195F188A502F448F2" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7F8547B47A71959EF514D88106FCD9D" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Bari and Nogol regions of NE Somalia (
<emphasis id="AD37BB75324012A038EFF4DCC7680D05" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Hansen &amp; Heemstra</emphasis>
6297, 
<emphasis id="350B2300532432B76C4402174B8E6800" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Becket</emphasis>
687, 
<emphasis id="BB66593C2887F4BBEE3220E559BA0FC0" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Nugent</emphasis>
33, 
<emphasis id="320AD1B56DA4BF17E36AA37DA1E4F79B" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Hemming</emphasis>
1866).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BE9213EC509DA7EB30888969A0F96E1B" lastPageId="130" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="notes">
<paragraph id="C069701058E56EB2617797EF1D804384" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="516EAB972D3B7AEED3EF48902418315D" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Occasional specimens intermediate with subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="482D06DB86731110691AB52C23506BA1" authorityName="Vahl, Symb. Bot. 1: 16. 1790. (Vahl" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hystrix">hystrix</taxonomicName>
are known from the same region (
<emphasis id="16E9D65CBA1AF9FD08670F5F50A7B9D3" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Lavranos &amp; Carter</emphasis>
24645, 
<emphasis id="EB9B4A3E2F15C874318B8938FE3D00EE" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Bally &amp; Melville</emphasis>
15450).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EDC2C1436CF8C44859858C00FFA15A3A" lastPageId="130" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Two other specimens from NE Somalia (
<emphasis id="CA96FA6874FD9E88D2E65C04558BBBDD" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<pageBreakToken id="5778793B623F8F5EC79C1D9AF371E788" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" start="start">Beckett</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
42, 
<emphasis id="D6E0E85986769E0453BC68E3721E5CE0" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Thulin et al</emphasis>
. 9488) are close to both 
<taxonomicName id="CF6F42371E8A14B9B10CCD8EED8CF86F" authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hystrix subsp. inermis" order="Solanales" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="hystrix" subSpecies="inermis">Convolvulus hystrix subsp. inermis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0CD9F22539B4F8E887220F8890133357" authorityName="Thulin, Nordic J. Bot. 23: 629. 2005. (Thulin" authorityYear="2005" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus scopulatus" order="Solanales" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopulatus">
<emphasis id="C8F90137DDD453486F2D9BC139AA1CC7" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Convolvulus scopulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They are similar in habit to both species but the stems and leaves are sericeous, the leaves oblong-lanceolate and the bracteoles similar to the leaves but acuminate to a fine point. They may represent an undescribed species or a form of 
<taxonomicName id="AFFD8A5C0F6B4DA13426BD2F2A9DC2DB" authorityName="Vahl, Symb. Bot. 1: 16. 1790. (Vahl" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hystrix">
<emphasis id="797B9FFCC5CEF65AA7611A0D77BF2BFC" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Convolvulus hystrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="8038D40BDFE52244BB767B5BC974788C" authorityName="Thulin, Nordic J. Bot. 23: 629. 2005. (Thulin" authorityYear="2005" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus scopulatus" order="Solanales" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopulatus">
<emphasis id="7EC3641E6BC2FC4EFDDCAEEE88A90463" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Convolvulus scopulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
